    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes works by the New Guinea Aboriginal Washkuk of the East Sepik Province in the Ambunti District. The Washkuk are well known for their distinctive male cult houses which contain carved structural elements, ornamentation, and furniture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045262/Grove Dictionary of Art online (1999-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000044868/Ethnologue [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describe varios tipos de obras de arte aborigen Washkuk de Nueva Guinea, de la provincia Sepik del este del distrito de Ambunti. Los Washkuk son muy conocidos por sus distintivas casas de culto masculino que contienen elementos esculturales tallados, ornamentación y muebles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beschrijft de diverse soorten kunstwerken van de Washkuk, oorspronkelijke bewoners van Nieuw-Guinea die leven in de provincie Oost-Sepik in het district Ambunti. De Washkuk zijn vooral bekend om hun opvallende mannenhuizen, met daarin beeldgesneden structuurelementen, ornamenten en meubilair.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>描述由安布恩提區境內東塞披省的新幾內亞瓦詩庫克土著所創作出來各式各樣的藝術作品。瓦詩庫克族是以他們獨具特色的男性膜拜房舍而聞名於世，房舍之中有著經過雕刻的結構性元素、裝飾品，以及家具。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
